ing build.gradle is set up with mail and jaxb libraries, probably because the tests involve certain classes that need them. However, jaxb is missing in JDK 25. The current build seems to have these libraries accounted for. \\n\\nNow, I’m thinking if the new OSGI version will affect this since the setup is meant to apply before generation. I wonder if starting with the normal generated scaffold will miss these extras. It’s all about deciding if the library needs any additional setup for proper coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dependency entries**\\n\\nI’m thinking we should probably include concrete entries rather than default ones. It's possible that the standard generator scaffold picks up dependencies based on what’s imported. However, the previous scaffold already has additional dependencies from earlier generations.  \\n\\nI wonder if the setup driver could add any extra dependency to the build.gradle file before the actual generation takes place. It’s a bit of a jigsaw puzzle figuring out how these pieces fit together!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating dependencies**\\n\\nI'm considering the necessary update to include the OSGi 4.2 dependency, despite potential old dependencies. It wouldn't help to mention mail/jaxb unless there are issues. The task requests researching resolved artifact dependencies, so I'll focus on all missing POM provided dependencies needed for meaningful tests. However, I want to keep the setup minimal and concrete. For now, I won’t take action unless there's concrete evidence. I should inspect the dynamic report for coverage, possibly regarding OSGi.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ee6bCAyu2eCTQ9xlP67Z9Gr6|fc_017bc0de7a1818cc016a42ff2d2ccc8197a0ee2fa14533c398", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.sun.jersey/jersey-core/1.9/dynamic-access-exhaust-report.json", "offset": 1, "limit": 160}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "us